# Contract Intelligence Platform - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

**Contract Intelligence Platform** is an AI-powered M&A due diligence contract analysis system built for PE-backed advisory firms. It ingests 200-500+ contracts per deal, extracts commercial terms, flags risks, and generates deal-ready deliverables (Excel matrices, PDF reports, PowerPoint summaries).

**Core Problem Solved:** Reducing contract review timelines from 3-4 weeks to 2-3 days with 97% risk flag recall.

## Tech Stack

### AI/LLM
- **Primary Model:** Claude API (3.5 Sonnet, Opus) - 200K context for full contracts
- **Fallback Model:** GPT-4 Turbo
- **Embeddings:** Voyage-law-2 (legal-domain optimized, 1024 dimensions)
- **Orchestration:** LangGraph (stateful AI agent graphs with human-in-the-loop)
- **Tracing & Evaluation:** LangSmith with custom evaluators (extraction F1, hallucination detection)

### Data & Search
- **Database:** Supabase PostgreSQL with pgvector extension
- **Vector Indexes:** HNSW (m=16, ef_construction=128) for 50M+ scale
- **Hybrid Search:** BM25 (full-text) + vector semantic + Cohere Reranking
- **Schema:** 12 tables (tenants, users, deals, contracts, clauses, embeddings, risk_flags, playbooks, audit_log, etc.)
- **RLS Policies:** Per-tenant isolation (each PE firm = one tenant)

### Document Processing
- **Native PDFs:** Docling (DocLayNet layout analysis, MIT license)
- **Scanned/OCR:** Azure Document Intelligence (99.8% accuracy)
- **Word Files:** python-docx
- **Chunking:** Clause-level hierarchical (200-500 tokens)
- **PII Redaction:** Microsoft Presidio (pre-processing, attorney-client privilege protection)

### Workflow & Automation
- **Async Jobs:** Trigger.dev (contract extraction, batch deal analysis)
- **Low-Code Workflows:** n8n (document ingestion, monitoring, Slack/email notifications)
- **Email Templates:** React Email
- **Email Delivery:** Resend (transactional emails)

### Auth & Frontend
- **Auth:** Clerk (SSO, SAML, passwordless, role-based access)
- **Frontend:** Next.js + shadcn/ui (dashboard, contract viewer, search interface)
- **PDF Viewer:** react-pdf-highlighter (inline clause highlighting, annotations)
- **Rich Text:** Tiptap (reviewer comments)

### Monitoring & Compliance
- **Deployment:** Vercel (Next.js frontend)
- **Error Tracking:** Sentry or equivalent
- **Audit Logging:** PostgreSQL audit_log table (immutable, compliance-ready)
- **Compliance:** SOC 2 Type II architecture (privacy, data residency, zero data retention)

## Architecture

### Multi-Tenant Data Model
```
Tenants (PE firms)
  ├── Users (partner, associate, analyst roles)
  ├── Deals (with deal_type, playbook_id)
  │   └── Contracts (with processing_status, parent_contract_id for amendments)
  │       ├── Clauses (40+ types with risk_level, confidence)
  │       ├── Clause Embeddings (vector(1024))
  │       ├── Contract Parties (normalized names for cross-deal matching)
  │       └── Risk Flags (flagged issues with severity and resolution)
  ├── Playbooks (deal-type-specific rule sets)
  └── Clause Library (market standards with centroid embeddings)
```

### AI Pipeline
1. **Classification:** Detect document type (contract, amendment, schedule, exhibit)
2. **Extraction:** Identify 40+ clause types (change of control, termination, indemnification, IP, etc.)
3. **Risk Scoring:** Flag non-standard terms, missing clauses, conflicting provisions
4. **Embedding:** Generate voyage-law-2 vectors for semantic search
5. **Cross-Reference:** Detect conflicts across full contract portfolio
6. **Human Review:** LangGraph routes low-confidence extractions (confidence < 0.85) to analysts

### Automation Workflows (n8n)
- **deal_room_ingestion.json:** Webhook → classify → extract → notify
- **extraction_monitoring.json:** Hourly audit of extraction quality via LangSmith

### Long-Running Jobs (Trigger.dev)
- **contract_extraction.ts:** Full pipeline per document (2-10 min) with checkpointing
- **deal_analysis.ts:** Batch processing with fan-out/fan-in for portfolio analysis

## Key Design Decisions

### Hybrid Search Strategy
- **Why:** Different user queries benefit from different approaches
  - Keyword queries ("unlimited liability") → BM25 full-text
  - Semantic queries ("what are the termination rights?") → vector search
  - Complex queries → Cohere Reranking combines both signals
- **Implementation:** Clause-level embeddings stored in pgvector, HNSW indexes

### Clause-Level Chunking
- **Why:** Legal documents have natural boundaries; preserves legal context and enables precise attribution
- **How:** 200-500 token chunks at clause boundaries with hierarchical metadata (section → subsection → clause)

### PII Redaction (Pre-Processing)
- **Why:** *United States v. Heppner* (2026) - AI-processed documents without PII redaction risk privilege waiver
- **How:** Presidio detects PII (confidence > 0.7) → anonymize before LLM processing → mapping table in encrypted storage for re-linking

### Multi-Model Routing
- **Why:** Different clause types benefit from different model strengths; fallback prevents single point of failure
- **How:** Classification → route to best-fit model (Claude for complex multi-section analysis, GPT-4 for standard extractions)

### Privilege Protection via Human-in-the-Loop
- **Why:** Attorney-client privilege requires human oversight
- **How:** Confidence < 0.85 routes to analyst review in LangGraph conditional edges; maintains audit trail

### pgvector over Dedicated Vector DB
- **Why:** Unified PostgreSQL stack (vectors + metadata + auth + RLS in one database); eliminates data sync complexity
- **How:** Supabase-hosted PostgreSQL with pgvector extension; RLS policies enforce tenant isolation

## Coding Conventions

### Python Code Style
- **Format:** Black (88-char line length)
- **Linting:** Flake8 + isort
- **Type hints:** Required for all functions and class methods
- **Docstrings:** Google-style for all public functions

### Project Structure
```
src/
  ├── orchestration/
  │   └── analysis_workflow.py (LangGraph graphs)
  ├── prompts/
  │   ├── clause_extraction.py (extraction prompts per clause type)
  │   ├── risk_scoring.py (risk assessment logic)
  │   └── cross_reference.py (conflict detection)
  ├── pipeline/
  │   ├── document_processor.py (Docling + Azure OCR)
  │   ├── clause_extractor.py (LLM extraction)
  │   ├── risk_scorer.py (confidence + risk mapping)
  │   └── embedder.py (voyage-law-2 generation)
  └── api/
      ├── auth.py (Clerk integration)
      ├── routes/
      │   ├── documents.py (upload, retrieve, delete)
      │   ├── search.py (hybrid semantic/keyword)
      │   ├── analysis.py (trigger extraction, export)
      │   └── review.py (human review endpoints)
      └── models.py (Pydantic schemas)
```

### LangSmith Integration
- **Decorator:** @traceable on all pipeline steps
- **Projects:** Named per environment (prod, staging, dev)
- **Datasets:** evaluation_extraction (F1 benchmarks), evaluation_risks (hallucination detection)
- **Custom Evaluators:** extract_accuracy, risk_flag_precision, conflict_detection_recall
- **Cost Tracking:** Per-extraction token counts and latency logged

### n8n Workflows
- **Naming:** snake_case JSON filenames matching function (deal_room_ingestion.json)
- **Error Handling:** Retry nodes with exponential backoff
- **Notifications:** Async via Resend (email) and Slack webhooks

### Trigger.dev Jobs
- **Naming:** PascalCase TypeScript files (ContractExtraction.ts)
- **Checkpointing:** Between each pipeline stage (classify → extract → score → cross-ref)
- **Error Handling:** Retry logic with dead-letter queue to audit_log

### React Email Templates
- **Location:** emails/*.tsx
- **Components:** Use @react-email/components only (no external CSS frameworks)
- **Props:** Typed with React.FC<EmailProps> interface
- **Testing:** render() + renderAsync() for preview

### Clerk Middleware
- **Location:** middleware.ts in Next.js root
- **Role Mapping:** Partner (full), Associate (review), Analyst (read-only)
- **Tenant Isolation:** Extract org_id from Clerk, set app.current_tenant for RLS

### Database Queries
- **ORM:** Supabase JS client for frontend, SQLAlchemy for Python backend
- **RLS:** Always include tenant_id in WHERE clause for enforcement
- **Migrations:** Use Supabase migration format (001_initial_schema.sql, etc.)
- **Indexes:** Composite indexes for (tenant_id, status) queries

### Secrets Management
- **Environment Variables:** .env.local (frontend), .env (backend)
- **Sensitive Keys:** Clerk publishable/secret, Supabase URL/key, LangSmith API key
- **Never Commit:** Use .env.example as template

## Critical Compliance Notes

### Attorney-Client Privilege
- PII must be redacted before LLM processing (Presidio)
- Human review required for confidence < 0.85 (LangGraph routing)
- Audit log is immutable and compliance-ready for discovery

### Tenant Isolation
- RLS policies enforce at database level (not application level)
- All queries must include tenant_id filtering
- Audit log records all cross-tenant queries (rare but detectable)

### Zero Data Retention
- All Claude/GPT-4 calls under ZDR (Zero Data Retention) agreements
- LLM responses not cached; re-run extraction for reproducibility
- LangSmith tracing is local/internal only (no external LLM evaluation)

### Export Compliance
- Generated reports contain no PII (use anonymized clause text)
- Excel matrices redact party names if sensitivity flag is set
- PDF/PPT exports include watermark "CONFIDENTIAL - ATTORNEY WORK PRODUCT"

## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests
- **Framework:** pytest
- **Mocks:** Mock LLM responses with pre-defined extractions
- **Coverage:** >80% for data layer, 60%+ for business logic

### Integration Tests
- **Database:** Use test Supabase instance
- **Fixtures:** Sample contracts in demo/sample_contracts/
- **Workflows:** Test LangGraph graphs with synthetic data

### Evaluation
- **LangSmith Datasets:** Run eval_extraction, eval_risks before production deploys
- **Metrics:** F1 >= 0.94 for extraction, recall >= 0.97 for risk flags

## Performance Targets

- **Clause Extraction:** < 10 minutes per 100-page contract
- **Cross-Reference Analysis:** < 5 minutes per 500-contract deal
- **Search:** < 500ms for hybrid queries on 50M+ vectors
- **Export Generation:** < 30 seconds for Excel matrix (500+ contracts)

## Deployment

- **Frontend:** Vercel (auto-deploys on main branch)
- **Backend:** Docker on AWS ECS (or equivalent) with auto-scaling
- **Database:** Supabase managed PostgreSQL
- **Orchestration:** Temporal for durable pipelines; Trigger.dev for background jobs

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Clerk SSO configured for tenant
- [ ] Supabase RLS policies enabled for all tenant tables
- [ ] PII redaction enabled in document processor
- [ ] LLM calls use ZDR agreements (no data retention)
- [ ] Audit log immutable and encrypted at rest
- [ ] CORS configured for frontend domain only
- [ ] API rate limiting enabled (100 req/min per user)
- [ ] Environment variables never logged
